        [
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "E-Learning",
          "Hybrid",
          "Next Exercise",
          "4217 ASSISTments09 learners, 574 Algebra 2005 learners, 335 OLIES students",
          "ASSISTments, Algebra and OLIES",
          "Sequence of Answers, Knowledge Components",
          "Learner knowledge is initialized via weighted-average of first-attempt scores on each concept.\n\nExercise profiles are created from difficulty and concept coverage",
          "Learner Mastery is updated after each attempt.",
          "Authors create a concept-exercise matrix that highlights the concepts covered by each exercise.\n\nStudent scores on each exercise are normalized",
          "Top-N exercises",
          "AST09\n{Accuracy: 0.866 - KCP-ER, Diversity: 0.772 - KCP-ER, Novelty: 0.963 - KCP-ER}\n\nAlgebra05\n{Accuracy: 0.899 - KCP-ER, Diversity: 0.751 - KCP-ER, Novelty: 0.839 - KCP-ER}\n\nOLIES\n{Accuracy: 0.894 - KCP-ER, Diversity: 0.948 - KCP-ER, Novelty: 0.883 - KCP-ER}",
          "Authors use Knowledge Tracing - and more specifically DKT to understand a learners’ mastery level of different concepts.\n\nThen, the authors compute similarity between exercises the suggest exercises that are in an approppriate difficulty for the knowledge concept.",
          "- Cognitive-level estimation estimation depends on manual tagging of exercises.\n\n- Does not use text of exercise to estimate difficulty (or correctedness)."
        ]
      ],
